description: Violent clashes ensued between protesters and the police in Gezi Park just hours after the Turkish prime minister said it would be cleared.
title: At Gezi Park, Tear Gas and Water Cannons
title_page: At Gezi Park, Tear Gas and Water Cannons - The New York Times
text: Protesters slept in the early morning in Gezi Park in Istanbul on Saturday. On Friday, a nonviolent end to the 18 days of antigovernment protests had briefly appeared possible.
